DMW boss, Davido Adeleke, has deposited approximately 36 million naira (100 thousand dollars) for luxury rings and jewellery for his gang members. The famous singer paid the huge sum in cash at a store in the USA just to get the famous 30BG rings and jewellery for his crew members. In a video which he uploaded on his Instagram stories, the son of Nigerian billionaire, Adedeji Adeleke, displayed some of the items that were being customized for them. On the rings and jewellery, the 30BG logo was boldly carved out along with the names of his manager, Asa Asika, his hypeman, Special Spesh, DJ Ecool and a few more. The crew would be getting the rings in a couple of weeks when everything would have been made ready See pictures below: